cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Lunheng (论衡): Multi-agent paper review framework anchored to top-tier journal rubrics"
abstract: >
  Lunheng is a contract-governed multi-agent paper review framework. Four
  specialist agents (Architect, Writer, Refiner, Evaluator-bench of 8
  dimensions) coordinate around a persistent visual contract that tracks
  figures, tables, terminology, and cross-references. Scoring uses anchored
  1-10 anchors per dimension, mapped to actual NeurIPS 2025 / Nature / JACS
  reviewer rubrics. Implemented as a pure Claude / Claude Code skill.
authors:
